      "review_summary": "The PR changes memory-core `status()` to infer vector-store availability from semantic chunks and adds a new seeded regression test file.\n\nPR surface: Source 0, Tests +175. Total +175 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level. Current main leaves `storeAvailable` undefined for a status-purpose manager before vector probing, plain status skips the probes, and the linked bug report shows matching plain/deep CLI output; I did not run a live CLI repro in this read-only pass.",
