      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(status): resolve \"Vector store: unknown\" on memory status fast path",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen memory status is queried without probing the vector store (status-only manager), `status().vector?.storeAvailable` returns `undefined` even when the vector store has been successfully built in a previous session. This causes \"Vector store: unknown\" in the status output.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`manager.ts:1152` used `this.vector.available ?? undefined` with no fallback. `vector.available` is only set by `probeVectorStoreAvailability()` or `ensureVectorReady()`, which are not called by the status-only path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### behavior\nChanged `storeAvailable` on status-only managers to fall back to `readMeta()?.vectorDims !== undefined` instead of always `undefined`. The `vectorDims` meta field is only written when vector writes succeed (manager-sync-ops.ts:2548), providing a reliable persisted signal of vector-store readiness.\n\n### environment\n- OS: Linux\n- Runtime: Node.js 22\n- Setup: OpenClaw worktree at commit 9918eff\n\n### steps\n1. Seed index DB with meta table containing `memory_index_meta_v1 = {\"vectorDims\": 768}`\n2. Create status-only manager (vector.available = null)\n3. Call `manager.status()` and inspect `storeAvailable`\n4. Repeat with empty meta `{}` — verify `storeAvailable` is undefined\n\n### observedResult\n\n**Test suite:**\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  2 passed (2)\n```\n\n**Test 1**: meta has vectorDims → storeAvailable = true ✓\n**Test 2**: meta has no vectorDims → storeAvailable = undefined ✓\n\n**Production change** (manager.ts:1152):\n```diff\n- storeAvailable: this.vector.available ?? (this.hasSemanticChunks() || undefined),\n+ storeAvailable: this.vector.available ?? (this.readMeta()?.vectorDims !== undefined || undefined),\n```\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm test --run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-has-semantic-chunks.test.ts` passes (2/2)\n- [x] Change is minimal — single line in manager.ts",
